* {{hyphenation|deu|te|ri|um|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{label|en|isotope}} An [[isotope]] of [[hydrogen]] formed of one [[proton]] and one [[neutron]] in each atom - {{nuclide|2|1|H}}.
#: ''[[heavy water|Heavy water]] is “heavy” because it contains '''deuterium'''.''
# An atom of this isotope.
#: ''There were about 80 '''deuteriums''' for every million protiums, and virtually no tritium.''

